      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "MISS LEOPATRA NZ (1) was good against the boys last start, coming from wider for fourth in the Group 3 Caduceus Club Classic. Had won three in a row here prior. Well placed back against her own sex and should enjoy a lovely run from the ace draw so looks hard to beat. TRIXIE DORA (6) hasn't had a lot go her way of late but did manage a win at this circuit and distance last month. Player with her A-game. THE SEA SIREN (5) has recorded a win and a placing in two previous third-up attempts so should be ready to produce her best. MISS BEJEWELED (4) was held up from a back row draw and and finished midfield when resuming. Fitter and her lone win came at this venue.",
